1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,302 --> 00:01:37,839
=Episode 18=
(Spring Festival Gala)

3
00:01:55,986 --> 00:02:01,016
(Ren Xiaoming asked me
to forward this to you.)

4
00:02:05,426 --> 00:02:08,984
(Qidaohezi, 2007)

5
00:02:08,984 --> 00:02:11,664
Xiaofei, is money really tight
at your home lately?

6
00:02:15,903 --> 00:02:18,143
Don't feel pressured.
I already figured it out.

7
00:02:18,504 --> 00:02:19,743
Money's always tight at home.

8
00:02:20,344 --> 00:02:22,423
When I was little,
they would smash my piggy bank

9
00:02:22,863 --> 00:02:23,824
to buy rice with coins.

10
00:02:24,384 --> 00:02:27,064
Another time, Xiaoming took me
to the government cafeteria

11
00:02:27,863 --> 00:02:29,344
to get discarded green pepper stems.

12
00:02:29,784 --> 00:02:32,824
We cooked them with soy sauce.
Went well with rice, tastier than meat.

13
00:02:33,384 --> 00:02:34,504
We ate those for months.

14
00:02:36,264 --> 00:02:38,903
Wasn't the bun business doing well?
Why stop suddenly?

15
00:02:40,344 --> 00:02:42,743
Mom told me not to mention it to you.

16
00:02:44,064 --> 00:02:44,743
Why?

17
00:02:45,344 --> 00:02:45,944
This one, boss.

18
00:02:46,064 --> 00:02:46,743
This place?

19
00:02:46,784 --> 00:02:47,623
Right here.

20
00:02:51,183 --> 00:02:52,023
Ren Meiyan!

21
00:02:52,023 --> 00:02:52,743
Open up! Open up!

22
00:02:52,743 --> 00:02:53,504
- Who are they?
- You thought turning off your phone

23
00:02:53,504 --> 00:02:54,423
- made it okay?
- From the Jinghe construction site.

24
00:02:54,583 --> 00:02:56,143
They claimed our buns were spoiled.

25
00:02:56,344 --> 00:02:57,080
Construction site?

26
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:58,224
They want my mom to pay.

27
00:02:58,224 --> 00:02:59,264
Jinghe construction site?

28
00:02:59,984 --> 00:03:01,544
Couldn't find you with your phone off?

29
00:03:01,583 --> 00:03:02,104
Your buns

30
00:03:02,104 --> 00:03:03,303
- made people sick!
- You're bullies!

31
00:03:03,784 --> 00:03:04,583
Xiaofei! Xiaofei!

32
00:03:05,064 --> 00:03:05,703
- Go inside.
- Open up!

33
00:03:05,743 --> 00:03:07,104
- Our buns were good!
- Xiaofei!

34
00:03:07,664 --> 00:03:08,824
- You're framing us!
- Xiaofei!

35
00:03:08,903 --> 00:03:10,784
Xiaofei, listen to me.

36
00:03:10,784 --> 00:03:11,423
Go inside first.

37
00:03:11,423 --> 00:03:11,923
Hurry!

38
00:03:12,104 --> 00:03:12,623
Xiaofei,

39
00:03:13,023 --> 00:03:13,863
- listen to me.
- Open up!

40
00:03:13,863 --> 00:03:15,423
Don't shout or get physical.

41
00:03:15,703 --> 00:03:16,344
Don't come out.

42
00:03:17,183 --> 00:03:18,384
- Come out!
- Come out!

43
00:03:18,403 --> 00:03:18,903
Open up!

44
00:03:18,903 --> 00:03:19,512
Come out now!

45
00:03:19,743 --> 00:03:20,344
Come out!

46
00:03:20,863 --> 00:03:21,743
- Come out!
- Come out!

47
00:03:22,264 --> 00:03:22,764
Come out!

48
00:03:26,143 --> 00:03:27,303
Where's Ren Meiyan?

49
00:03:27,703 --> 00:03:28,583
She's not here.

50
00:03:28,863 --> 00:03:31,784
Not here? Guys, smash this place!

51
00:03:31,984 --> 00:03:33,183
Don't you dare!

52
00:03:37,423 --> 00:03:38,784
You're collecting for someone.

53
00:03:39,384 --> 00:03:40,544
Smash the place, and you pay.

54
00:03:41,384 --> 00:03:43,183
Will the person who sent you
pay for that?

55
00:03:43,784 --> 00:03:45,423
Hurt someone, and you go to jail.

56
00:03:45,703 --> 00:03:47,064
The money collected isn't yours.

57
00:03:47,623 --> 00:03:48,903
But you pay and do the time.

58
00:03:50,344 --> 00:03:51,064
What's the point?

59
00:03:51,064 --> 00:03:52,903
Who the heck are you?

60
00:03:53,023 --> 00:03:55,264
Aren't you just a little girl
from the community?

61
00:03:56,544 --> 00:03:57,104
How much?

62
00:03:59,824 --> 00:04:00,903
How much money?

63
00:04:02,423 --> 00:04:03,903
Thirty-six thousand.

64
00:04:05,703 --> 00:04:07,423
Hospital receipts?
Show me the breakdown.

65
00:04:08,224 --> 00:04:09,104
Go inside. Go inside.

66
00:04:09,264 --> 00:04:12,544
What's a little girl like you
looking at a breakdown for?

67
00:04:12,664 --> 00:04:13,703
Plus lost wages.

68
00:04:13,984 --> 00:04:15,264
And lost wages.

69
00:04:15,384 --> 00:04:15,884
Yeah.

70
00:04:15,984 --> 00:04:17,224
There's also lost wages.

71
00:04:17,383 --> 00:04:19,224
All of us wasted our time, right?

72
00:04:19,224 --> 00:04:20,943
There's lost wages, you know?

73
00:04:23,224 --> 00:04:25,423
Xiaofei, go get me paper and a pen.

74
00:04:28,344 --> 00:04:29,183
To write an IOU?

75
00:04:40,823 --> 00:04:41,383
Go there.

76
00:04:42,344 --> 00:04:43,383
Give this note to her

77
00:04:44,784 --> 00:04:46,024
and ask her for the money.

78
00:04:46,610 --> 00:04:48,888
(I won't come home until you fix this.
Building 23, Roman Elegance)

79
00:04:52,544 --> 00:04:53,904
You know Ms. Ge?

80
00:04:55,904 --> 00:04:59,183
She knows deep down
whether she should pay this money.

81
00:05:00,263 --> 00:05:01,503
Maybe you know too.

82
00:05:02,503 --> 00:05:03,863
I send you to ask her for it

83
00:05:04,784 --> 00:05:06,503
because I have reason and evidence.

84
00:05:08,063 --> 00:05:10,984
You... What's your relationship
with Ms. Ge?

85
00:05:12,344 --> 00:05:14,183
What you should be worried about now

86
00:05:14,904 --> 00:05:17,584
is how many years in prison
you'll get for what you've done.

87
00:05:18,503 --> 00:05:19,063
Let's go.

88
00:05:19,183 --> 00:05:19,904
Let's go.

89
00:05:20,664 --> 00:05:21,303
Let's go.

90
00:05:22,183 --> 00:05:22,823
Hurry up.

91
00:05:23,544 --> 00:05:24,584
Let's go.

92
00:05:27,344 --> 00:05:30,623
Bai Shu, what did you say?
He listened to you so well.

93
00:05:31,344 --> 00:05:33,104
I said he was framing us,
which is illegal.

94
00:05:33,984 --> 00:05:34,544
Awesome.

95
00:05:37,024 --> 00:05:39,704
Did your mom tell you
why those people framed her?

96
00:05:40,503 --> 00:05:41,144
No.

97
00:05:44,024 --> 00:05:45,080
About what happened today,

98
00:05:45,503 --> 00:05:47,503
don't tell your mom or sister, okay?

99
00:05:48,104 --> 00:05:49,063
Why can't I tell them?

100
00:05:50,503 --> 00:05:52,544
They kept the bun thing from me

101
00:05:52,584 --> 00:05:53,823
to not trouble me.

102
00:05:54,784 --> 00:05:55,904
I'll pretend not to know.

103
00:05:56,263 --> 00:05:57,104
Easier for everyone.

104
00:05:57,584 --> 00:05:58,584
But the troublemakers...

105
00:05:58,904 --> 00:06:00,063
They won't be coming back.

106
00:06:01,784 --> 00:06:03,344
Alright, I won't say anything.

107
00:06:04,584 --> 00:06:05,383
Bai Shu,

108
00:06:06,183 --> 00:06:07,503
will you suddenly leave?

109
00:06:11,224 --> 00:06:11,863
I won't.

110
00:06:12,584 --> 00:06:14,503
A family should
celebrate the New Year together.

111
00:06:15,003 --> 00:06:16,423
Let's go and tidy up the place.

112
00:07:05,746 --> 00:07:07,183
(Chinese New Year's Eve,
February 17, 2007)

113
00:07:07,183 --> 00:07:08,503
Meiyan, Happy Chinese New Year!

114
00:07:08,623 --> 00:07:10,063
Happy Chinese New Year!

115
00:07:10,584 --> 00:07:12,623
Ren Xiaoming! Ren Xiaofei!

116
00:07:13,224 --> 00:07:14,503
Come down and get the things.

117
00:07:14,623 --> 00:07:15,503
Coming! Coming!

118
00:07:16,503 --> 00:07:18,024
I told you your hair needed a perm.

119
00:07:18,984 --> 00:07:19,503
How is it?

120
00:07:19,576 --> 00:07:20,120
My hands.

121
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:21,400
Did my name get you a discount?

122
00:07:21,904 --> 00:07:22,623
No.

123
00:07:22,904 --> 00:07:23,623
No?

124
00:07:23,823 --> 00:07:24,863
Hurry up and come down.

125
00:07:25,816 --> 00:07:28,704
I was waiting for the cabbage.
I'll go to cook. Happy Chinese New Year!

126
00:07:28,704 --> 00:07:29,112
Mom.

127
00:07:29,112 --> 00:07:30,392
Ma'am. Happy Chinese New Year!

128
00:07:30,392 --> 00:07:31,704
Happy Chinese New Year!

129
00:07:31,823 --> 00:07:33,024
Why are you so late?

130
00:07:33,024 --> 00:07:34,344
Ma'am, you got a perm?

131
00:07:34,823 --> 00:07:37,024
Zhang Fang's mom dragged me
to get it done.

132
00:07:38,144 --> 00:07:40,823
We can barely afford food,
yet you got a perm.

133
00:07:41,383 --> 00:07:42,263
It looks really nice.

134
00:07:43,183 --> 00:07:45,303
Such a sweet girl. I have gifts for you.

135
00:07:47,503 --> 00:07:50,104
One red scarf each.

136
00:07:51,224 --> 00:07:52,224
Thank you, ma'am.

137
00:07:53,743 --> 00:07:58,224
For a prosperous Chinese New Year.
This one's for my daughter.

138
00:08:00,544 --> 00:08:04,024
Buy three, get one free.
Thanks to you, I got one too.

139
00:08:04,344 --> 00:08:05,144
Put it on.

140
00:08:06,623 --> 00:08:07,623
The quality is top-notch.

141
00:08:08,823 --> 00:08:09,704
And more gifts.

142
00:08:11,183 --> 00:08:11,823
What is it?

143
00:08:12,823 --> 00:08:15,063
One pair of lucky red socks each.

144
00:08:16,144 --> 00:08:17,303
And socks too?

145
00:08:17,584 --> 00:08:19,544
Red from head to toe.

146
00:08:20,584 --> 00:08:21,084
Here you go.

147
00:08:21,263 --> 00:08:22,984
All this red?

148
00:08:23,063 --> 00:08:24,943
Couldn't you have picked
something more elegant?

149
00:08:25,344 --> 00:08:26,503
Prosperous Chinese New Year.

150
00:08:26,503 --> 00:08:27,303
- It's good.
- Take them.

151
00:08:29,423 --> 00:08:30,503
I'm cooking the dinner.

152
00:08:30,823 --> 00:08:32,824
I'll walk elegantly forward.

153
00:08:37,304 --> 00:08:38,863
Oh my goodness, such small fish.

154
00:08:40,383 --> 00:08:41,224
So tiny.

155
00:08:41,783 --> 00:08:43,023
Nothing but bones, right?

156
00:08:43,543 --> 00:08:44,304
So miniature.

157
00:08:44,824 --> 00:08:47,464
Don't be picky.
We're lucky to have found any.

158
00:08:48,184 --> 00:08:49,424
The market was packed.

159
00:08:49,424 --> 00:08:51,128
People queued
even for the priciest items.

160
00:08:51,128 --> 00:08:52,344
Forget about fish or chicken.

161
00:08:52,863 --> 00:08:54,704
Even Boston lobsters were sold out.

162
00:08:54,704 --> 00:08:56,283
Small fish taste great fried.

163
00:08:56,464 --> 00:08:56,984
Right.

164
00:08:57,503 --> 00:09:00,783
It's not that we can't afford it.
Our tastes are just very particular.

165
00:09:01,503 --> 00:09:02,743
Admit it. We can't afford it.

166
00:09:07,224 --> 00:09:08,704
Fried little fish.

167
00:09:15,503 --> 00:09:19,304
Auspicious snow heralds a good harvest.
Spring wind welcomes the new year.

168
00:09:19,464 --> 00:09:21,143
As we ring out the old
and ring in the new,

169
00:09:21,464 --> 00:09:23,464
we wish Ren Meiyan's family in Qidaohezi

170
00:09:23,704 --> 00:09:25,704
a Happy Chinese New Year,
family happiness,

171
00:09:25,863 --> 00:09:27,944
good fortune, and prosperity!

172
00:09:27,984 --> 00:09:28,484
Cheers!

173
00:09:28,584 --> 00:09:29,084
Cheers!

174
00:09:29,184 --> 00:09:30,344
Cheers!

175
00:09:34,704 --> 00:09:35,344
Let's eat.

176
00:09:38,344 --> 00:09:39,143
Stop grabbing.

177
00:09:39,743 --> 00:09:40,824
Stop grabbing.

178
00:09:41,704 --> 00:09:42,984
Bai Shu first.

179
00:09:42,984 --> 00:09:44,023
Thank you, Ma'am.

180
00:09:44,464 --> 00:09:45,584
I meant it for Bai Shu.

181
00:09:45,584 --> 00:09:46,424
Me too.

182
00:09:47,023 --> 00:09:47,623
Eat.

183
00:09:48,944 --> 00:09:50,444
Ma'am, I'd like to toast you.

184
00:09:50,944 --> 00:09:52,944
Look, look.
This is what filial piety looks like.

185
00:09:52,944 --> 00:09:54,503
You two only think about eating.

186
00:09:55,064 --> 00:09:55,984
Ma'am, thank you.

187
00:09:56,383 --> 00:09:58,663
I wish you health, happiness, and joy.

188
00:09:59,383 --> 00:10:01,503
Good girl, no need for thanks.

189
00:10:01,984 --> 00:10:05,824
I also wish you success in studies,
good health, and a happy heart.

190
00:10:06,503 --> 00:10:07,104
Thank you.

191
00:10:08,824 --> 00:10:09,944
My turn to be a good kid.

192
00:10:10,543 --> 00:10:11,383
Say something nice.

193
00:10:14,344 --> 00:10:16,424
Then I wish you make a fortune
in the new year,

194
00:10:16,743 --> 00:10:18,824
win the lottery head up,
and find a wallet head down,

195
00:10:19,184 --> 00:10:20,984
so I can become a rich heiress sooner.

196
00:10:22,263 --> 00:10:25,424
Are you wishing me well
or planning for yourself?

197
00:10:25,424 --> 00:10:26,304
Hurry up.

198
00:10:26,304 --> 00:10:27,464
Say something nice back.

199
00:10:27,464 --> 00:10:28,383
Okay.

200
00:10:28,464 --> 00:10:29,464
I wish you...

201
00:10:30,424 --> 00:10:31,623
I wish you

202
00:10:31,944 --> 00:10:33,023
wouldn't cause any trouble,

203
00:10:33,383 --> 00:10:35,824
get into college smoothly,
and find a good job

204
00:10:36,064 --> 00:10:37,684
to support me sooner. Clap!

205
00:10:41,383 --> 00:10:41,944
My turn.

206
00:10:42,863 --> 00:10:45,383
This is rare.
Let's listen to what my son says.

207
00:10:45,863 --> 00:10:47,383
I wish you wouldn't overwork yourself

208
00:10:48,023 --> 00:10:50,743
or feel wronged. May you be happy inside
and comfortable outside.

209
00:10:51,344 --> 00:10:52,424
May all be well with you.

210
00:10:59,143 --> 00:11:00,743
I'm not tired or wronged.

211
00:11:00,863 --> 00:11:02,663
If you two are fine, I'm fine.

212
00:11:03,944 --> 00:11:04,464
Xiaofei,

213
00:11:07,863 --> 00:11:08,464
I wish you...

214
00:11:08,584 --> 00:11:09,604
Wait. Hold on.

215
00:11:11,104 --> 00:11:12,023
Don't tear it.

216
00:11:12,023 --> 00:11:12,944
Give it to me.

217
00:11:13,224 --> 00:11:14,184
Hold it back. No crying.

218
00:11:16,663 --> 00:11:17,704
If she cries,

219
00:11:17,944 --> 00:11:19,503
we won't make a fortune next year.

220
00:11:19,863 --> 00:11:20,863
Not crying. Not crying.

221
00:11:21,464 --> 00:11:22,783
Mom, don't be sad.

222
00:11:23,944 --> 00:11:24,743
I'm not sad.

223
00:11:24,824 --> 00:11:26,743
I'm happy you're so sensible.

224
00:11:27,903 --> 00:11:30,143
Then see how sensible I am.
Are you happy?

225
00:11:30,304 --> 00:11:31,104
Go away.

226
00:11:33,503 --> 00:11:35,023
Old tabby cat meowing away.

227
00:11:35,224 --> 00:11:36,312
Now crying, then laughing.

228
00:11:36,543 --> 00:11:37,783
Meow, meow, meow.

229
00:11:39,304 --> 00:11:40,663
Eat up, Bai Shu.

230
00:11:48,263 --> 00:11:48,944
Fireworks!

231
00:11:52,464 --> 00:11:53,944
Setting off fireworks so early?

232
00:12:18,064 --> 00:12:22,304
The Ren Meiyan family's
Spring Festival Gala begins now!

233
00:12:22,863 --> 00:12:24,344
Foot washing time!

234
00:12:24,383 --> 00:12:25,543
Foot washing time!

235
00:12:25,543 --> 00:12:28,224
Wash your feet clean
for good luck in the new year.

236
00:12:28,543 --> 00:12:30,383
Hurry up. I've given you my washbasin.

237
00:12:30,704 --> 00:12:31,543
Come on.

238
00:12:31,543 --> 00:12:32,783
One, two, three!

239
00:12:36,424 --> 00:12:38,143
Your basin is way too small.

240
00:12:38,623 --> 00:12:39,944
Let's play hot potato.

241
00:12:40,964 --> 00:12:41,464
Okay.

242
00:12:41,464 --> 00:12:42,064
Okay.

243
00:12:42,064 --> 00:12:43,184
Here we go.

244
00:12:44,143 --> 00:12:44,643
Pass...

245
00:12:44,743 --> 00:12:45,824
- Pass the apple.
- Pass the apple.

246
00:12:47,143 --> 00:12:47,743
Come on.

247
00:12:48,023 --> 00:12:49,023
One, two, three.

248
00:12:54,863 --> 00:12:56,184
Why is it you?

249
00:12:56,424 --> 00:12:57,543
What do you mean, 'why me'?

250
00:12:57,584 --> 00:12:58,503
You're everywhere.

251
00:12:58,503 --> 00:12:59,984
Fine, you're first. You win.

252
00:13:00,023 --> 00:13:00,523
Come on.

253
00:13:00,704 --> 00:13:01,543
Ready? Go.

254
00:13:05,304 --> 00:13:06,543
Why you again?

255
00:13:06,783 --> 00:13:07,663
You're everywhere.

256
00:13:07,944 --> 00:13:08,623
- You keep it.
- For me?

257
00:13:08,623 --> 00:13:09,123
Not for her.

258
00:13:09,383 --> 00:13:09,883
Okay.

259
00:13:10,104 --> 00:13:10,704
Go!

260
00:13:17,224 --> 00:13:18,224
- Everyone
- It's me.

261
00:13:18,224 --> 00:13:19,944
is first place.

262
00:13:20,944 --> 00:13:23,224
Next event: put on red socks.

263
00:13:23,503 --> 00:13:26,543
See who puts them on fastest.
The fastest gets a reward.

264
00:13:26,663 --> 00:13:29,464
It's the big prize, our grand prize.

265
00:13:30,464 --> 00:13:31,304
Dry your feet first.

266
00:13:34,304 --> 00:13:35,023
Dry your feet.

267
00:13:37,783 --> 00:13:38,424
I'm done drying.

268
00:13:38,424 --> 00:13:39,944
Okay. Are your socks ready?

269
00:13:39,984 --> 00:13:40,944
- Yes.
- Yes.

270
00:13:40,944 --> 00:13:42,184
On three, pull them out.

271
00:13:42,184 --> 00:13:44,064
- Okay.
- One, two, three.

272
00:13:50,224 --> 00:13:51,543
One, two, three, put them on.

273
00:13:58,383 --> 00:13:59,344
Almost done, almost.

274
00:13:59,623 --> 00:14:00,123
I'm first!

275
00:14:00,444 --> 00:14:00,944
I'm first!

276
00:14:00,944 --> 00:14:01,424
Got them on!

277
00:14:01,424 --> 00:14:02,704
- I'm first!
- I'm first!

278
00:14:02,743 --> 00:14:03,503
I'm first too!

279
00:14:03,503 --> 00:14:04,104
I'm first!

280
00:14:04,184 --> 00:14:05,224
All done?

281
00:14:05,224 --> 00:14:05,984
I'm first!

282
00:14:05,984 --> 00:14:08,824
I declare the Ren Meiyan family
all first place!

283
00:14:09,224 --> 00:14:12,663
But how should we
split this single grand prize?

284
00:14:13,184 --> 00:14:14,023
As family head,

285
00:14:14,344 --> 00:14:16,663
I propose
dividing the grand prize equally.

286
00:14:17,944 --> 00:14:19,023
Do you all agree?

287
00:14:21,023 --> 00:14:22,023
Fortune arrives!

288
00:14:22,743 --> 00:14:23,944
Let's see how much is inside.

289
00:14:23,984 --> 00:14:25,304
You can imagine.

290
00:14:28,503 --> 00:14:29,663
Thirty yuan.

291
00:14:31,383 --> 00:14:33,464
Ten yuan for Bai Shu.

292
00:14:33,464 --> 00:14:34,424
Thanks, Ma'am.

293
00:14:34,984 --> 00:14:36,584
Xiaoming, my daughter.

294
00:14:36,944 --> 00:14:37,704
Thank you.

295
00:14:37,824 --> 00:14:39,023
- My son, ten yuan.
- Thanks.

296
00:14:39,023 --> 00:14:39,743
Thanks, Mom.

297
00:14:40,304 --> 00:14:41,984
I only have an empty envelope left.

298
00:14:42,344 --> 00:14:43,543
Mom, I'm giving you mine.

299
00:14:43,824 --> 00:14:44,503
Thank you.

300
00:14:45,104 --> 00:14:45,984
You gave it to me?

301
00:14:46,424 --> 00:14:47,143
Take mine too.

302
00:14:47,184 --> 00:14:47,824
Ma'am.

303
00:14:48,263 --> 00:14:48,944
All for me?

304
00:14:50,104 --> 00:14:51,464
I won the jackpot.

305
00:14:52,184 --> 00:14:54,783
I won the jackpot tonight.

306
00:15:04,543 --> 00:15:07,503
The Ren Meiyan family's
Spring Festival Gala ends here.

307
00:15:07,824 --> 00:15:10,184
We'll meet again next year.

308
00:15:10,424 --> 00:15:12,944
Wishing you all a good night.

309
00:15:36,383 --> 00:15:38,743
- Happy Chinese New Year!
- Happy Chinese New Year!

310
00:15:42,304 --> 00:15:43,224
Happy Chinese New Year!

311
00:15:43,944 --> 00:15:44,920
Happy Chinese New Year!

312
00:15:56,383 --> 00:15:56,984
Let's have

313
00:15:58,464 --> 00:15:59,424
a little private chat.

314
00:16:00,424 --> 00:16:01,184
About what?

315
00:16:07,543 --> 00:16:09,464
We're about to go to college,

316
00:16:10,184 --> 00:16:11,383
basically adults now.

317
00:16:11,824 --> 00:16:13,743
Let's talk about something more mature.

318
00:16:14,543 --> 00:16:15,424
Like what?

319
00:16:15,944 --> 00:16:17,624
Have you ever thought about dating?

320
00:16:20,536 --> 00:16:21,663
So that's the topic?

321
00:16:22,104 --> 00:16:24,143
You just want to talk about He Yuqiong.

322
00:16:25,344 --> 00:16:26,743
Bai Shu,

323
00:16:27,304 --> 00:16:28,824
why are you as vulgar as my mom?

324
00:16:28,944 --> 00:16:29,743
I won't talk to you.

325
00:16:29,924 --> 00:16:31,383
Sorry, I shouldn't have joked.

326
00:16:31,464 --> 00:16:32,184
Then tell me,

327
00:16:33,023 --> 00:16:34,023
any thoughts on love?

328
00:16:37,383 --> 00:16:39,863
I think love
shouldn't be utilitarian at all.

329
00:16:40,263 --> 00:16:41,723
My mom was too utilitarian.

330
00:16:41,723 --> 00:16:43,184
She married so many men,

331
00:16:43,623 --> 00:16:45,143
not one she truly loved.

332
00:16:46,023 --> 00:16:47,224
Not even your dad?

333
00:16:48,503 --> 00:16:50,064
When I was little, I heard Grandma say

334
00:16:51,263 --> 00:16:54,584
my mom married my dad
to go to Guangzhou and see the world.

335
00:16:54,944 --> 00:16:56,104
I totally believe that.

336
00:16:56,743 --> 00:16:57,743
That's who my mom is.

337
00:16:58,263 --> 00:16:59,704
But if your mom is that utilitarian,

338
00:17:00,184 --> 00:17:01,623
why would she keep me at your place?

339
00:17:01,863 --> 00:17:03,304
It is risky.

340
00:17:04,464 --> 00:17:08,303
What risk? You're talking nonsense.

341
00:17:09,783 --> 00:17:10,583
I haven't finished.

342
00:17:10,583 --> 00:17:11,664
Then go ahead.

343
00:17:12,664 --> 00:17:13,424
I have to

344
00:17:14,023 --> 00:17:16,704
love someone very, very, very,

345
00:17:16,823 --> 00:17:17,944
very much.

346
00:17:19,023 --> 00:17:20,464
Otherwise, I wouldn't get married.

347
00:17:21,944 --> 00:17:24,944
It has to be that kind of genuine love.

348
00:17:25,464 --> 00:17:26,783
How do you know it's genuine?

349
00:17:29,424 --> 00:17:30,144
It hurts.

350
00:17:31,823 --> 00:17:33,984
That is, when he says he loves me,

351
00:17:35,984 --> 00:17:37,184
my heart

352
00:17:38,184 --> 00:17:39,624
throbs painfully.

353
00:17:45,103 --> 00:17:46,944
Are you sure it's not a heart attack?

354
00:17:48,823 --> 00:17:51,783
Bai Shu, why do you keep teasing me?

355
00:17:52,144 --> 00:17:53,543
No more teasing. No teasing.

356
00:17:56,704 --> 00:17:57,464
Then you tell me,

357
00:17:58,343 --> 00:18:00,063
what do you think love is?

358
00:18:02,944 --> 00:18:05,184
I don't want to date or get married.

359
00:18:06,543 --> 00:18:07,224
Why?

360
00:18:11,144 --> 00:18:12,464
People even abandon their kids.

361
00:18:14,103 --> 00:18:15,583
What human emotion is eternal?

362
00:18:20,823 --> 00:18:23,664
What about the promise between us?

363
00:18:24,384 --> 00:18:25,704
Always together, never apart,

364
00:18:26,424 --> 00:18:27,864
and share this pen together.

365
00:18:30,783 --> 00:18:32,503
You never know what a lifetime holds.

366
00:18:33,384 --> 00:18:36,343
Maybe we won't be able to see
or talk to each other again.

367
00:18:37,944 --> 00:18:40,384
But we should still trust
and not betray each other.

368
00:18:43,944 --> 00:18:44,704
Okay.

369
00:18:47,023 --> 00:18:48,263
Then we need a way

370
00:18:48,263 --> 00:18:50,424
to communicate
that only you and I understand.

371
00:18:50,624 --> 00:18:51,743
That way, even if one day

372
00:18:51,984 --> 00:18:54,543
we can't talk or see each other,

373
00:18:54,783 --> 00:18:57,583
we can still know
what the other is thinking.

374
00:19:00,424 --> 00:19:01,664
Do you know about Nüshu?

375
00:19:02,704 --> 00:19:04,704
It's a special script

376
00:19:04,944 --> 00:19:06,783
used by women to pass messages.

377
00:19:08,464 --> 00:19:11,063
That's so cool. Can you write it?

378
00:19:11,543 --> 00:19:12,144
No.

379
00:19:14,144 --> 00:19:17,384
But we can use a code.

380
00:19:24,823 --> 00:19:26,680
I have
A Hundred Years of Different Paths too.

381
00:19:26,823 --> 00:19:27,783
Ms. Zhou gave it to me.

382
00:19:28,184 --> 00:19:29,528
We'll use it as the master copy.

383
00:19:30,424 --> 00:19:31,184
Master copy?

384
00:19:32,543 --> 00:19:33,583
I know.

385
00:19:34,023 --> 00:19:36,664
It's in The Adventures
of Sherlock Holmes.

386
00:19:38,303 --> 00:19:40,743
Each word is represented
by three sets of numbers:

387
00:19:41,864 --> 00:19:45,503
page number, line number,

388
00:19:45,704 --> 00:19:47,263
and position from the right.

389
00:19:47,384 --> 00:19:48,063
Let's try it.

390
00:19:48,343 --> 00:19:48,843
Okay.

391
00:19:49,103 --> 00:19:49,823
Me first.

392
00:19:49,864 --> 00:19:50,424
Okay.

393
00:20:04,523 --> 00:20:05,023
Here.

394
00:20:05,023 --> 00:20:05,523
You're done?

395
00:20:06,944 --> 00:20:07,583
Alright.

396
00:20:07,624 --> 00:20:09,944
Let me see what you wrote.

397
00:20:12,023 --> 00:20:12,523
I

398
00:20:16,503 --> 00:20:17,003
let

399
00:20:20,823 --> 00:20:21,323
out

400
00:20:24,424 --> 00:20:25,224
a

401
00:20:28,384 --> 00:20:28,984
fart?

402
00:20:29,984 --> 00:20:31,384
How did you know,

403
00:20:31,384 --> 00:20:32,063
Bai Shu?

404
00:20:32,063 --> 00:20:33,103
- You didn't use the numbers.
- Ren Xiaoming,

405
00:20:33,103 --> 00:20:35,103
you're such a fart machine.

406
00:20:35,103 --> 00:20:37,263
How come you can fart so much?

407
00:20:37,664 --> 00:20:38,424
Your turn.

408
00:20:38,543 --> 00:20:39,704
Okay, my turn.

409
00:20:40,343 --> 00:20:41,263
I'll write it well.

410
00:20:41,843 --> 00:20:43,144
Go sit over there.

411
00:21:07,063 --> 00:21:10,984
Are you writing an essay?
It's taking forever.

412
00:21:11,464 --> 00:21:14,023
Are there even enough characters
in this book for you to use?

413
00:21:14,984 --> 00:21:16,624
I need to challenge myself.

414
00:21:17,503 --> 00:21:19,303
Unlike you,
who dismissed me with a fart.

415
00:22:40,263 --> 00:22:41,464
Staying up for New Year?

416
00:22:43,664 --> 00:22:46,184
You slept like the dead,
yet you talk about staying up?

417
00:22:55,343 --> 00:22:58,743
Bai Shu? Hurry up. My stomach hurts.

418
00:23:00,583 --> 00:23:01,144
Bai Shu?

419
00:23:05,144 --> 00:23:06,343
I'm coming in.

420
00:23:45,103 --> 00:23:47,783
(Xiaoming, I've decided to go back.)

421
00:23:48,583 --> 00:23:51,263
(These days, I felt freedom,)

422
00:23:51,424 --> 00:23:52,464
(and I felt love.)

423
00:23:53,343 --> 00:23:54,984
(But I can't be a dependent.)

424
00:23:55,783 --> 00:23:58,664
(I can't shift my troubles
onto someone else.)

425
00:23:59,704 --> 00:24:02,944
(Otherwise, how am I any different
from that person?)

426
00:24:04,543 --> 00:24:07,464
(I'm going back, but I won't give up.)

427
00:24:08,503 --> 00:24:09,984
(This is just a temporary goodbye.)

428
00:24:10,984 --> 00:24:12,424
(We'll see each other again.)

429
00:24:30,343 --> 00:24:31,664
Why all the crying so early?

430
00:24:36,783 --> 00:24:37,283
Xiaoming?

431
00:24:40,424 --> 00:24:41,184
What's wrong?

432
00:24:41,543 --> 00:24:43,543
Bai Shu left.

433
00:24:46,944 --> 00:24:47,904
Don't cry.

434
00:24:48,743 --> 00:24:52,543
Listen, crying on Chinese New Year's Day
means you won't have a good year.

435
00:24:55,424 --> 00:24:57,144
Bai Shu probably has something to do.

436
00:24:57,144 --> 00:24:58,103
Why are you crying?

437
00:25:06,144 --> 00:25:06,944
Hello?

438
00:25:07,944 --> 00:25:08,543
Who is it?

439
00:25:18,464 --> 00:25:19,144
Yuxiu?

440
00:25:19,583 --> 00:25:20,503
Is that you, Yuxiu?

441
00:25:27,424 --> 00:25:28,103
Yuxiu?

442
00:26:10,424 --> 00:26:11,424
You said

443
00:26:11,743 --> 00:26:14,063
if I helped solve
Ren Xiaoming's family's trouble,

444
00:26:14,944 --> 00:26:16,864
you would come back
on Chinese New Year Day.

445
00:26:17,664 --> 00:26:19,464
You did it, and I did it.

446
00:26:20,184 --> 00:26:22,583
How about it?
Their New Year went well, didn't it?

447
00:26:23,224 --> 00:26:24,343
No one went to collect, huh?

448
00:26:29,984 --> 00:26:32,023
(Invoices)
I covered the worker's medical bills

449
00:26:33,303 --> 00:26:35,464
and the compensation for nutrition
and lost wages.

450
00:26:36,624 --> 00:26:38,303
The construction site is all set.

451
00:26:39,583 --> 00:26:42,424
I also paid the fine from the authority.

452
00:26:44,224 --> 00:26:45,783
To run a proper business,

453
00:26:46,184 --> 00:26:49,103
she should go get
a proper business license.

454
00:26:52,144 --> 00:26:54,583
I also took care
of Ren Xiaoming's sponsorship fee

455
00:26:55,144 --> 00:26:56,184
at school.

456
00:26:57,224 --> 00:26:59,063
I even spoke with her homeroom teacher.

457
00:26:59,984 --> 00:27:01,664
She'll get extra help before the gaokao.

458
00:27:04,944 --> 00:27:05,624
Well?

459
00:27:06,624 --> 00:27:08,303
Are you satisfied with what I've done?

460
00:27:13,583 --> 00:27:14,823
What's that?

461
00:27:17,184 --> 00:27:20,464
There's a major national project
down in Hainan.

462
00:27:20,904 --> 00:27:24,583
The construction company invited me
to join their quality inspection team.

463
00:27:26,063 --> 00:27:27,984
We can stay there for over three months.

464
00:27:29,224 --> 00:27:30,424
It's by the sea.

465
00:27:31,783 --> 00:27:32,343
Right,

466
00:27:33,343 --> 00:27:34,823
you can learn to scuba dive there.

467
00:27:35,424 --> 00:27:37,464
Want to learn?
I'll sign you up for a diving class.

468
00:27:40,224 --> 00:27:41,103
Leave right now?

469
00:27:41,343 --> 00:27:41,984
Yes.

470
00:27:44,343 --> 00:27:45,664
Aren't you watering the plants?

471
00:27:46,224 --> 00:27:48,543
The plants at home are hungry.
We'll be gone a long time.

472
00:27:49,144 --> 00:27:50,384
Let them eat their fill.

473
00:28:00,224 --> 00:28:00,904
What?

474
00:28:01,583 --> 00:28:03,543
Afraid that once we leave,
we won't come back,

475
00:28:04,864 --> 00:28:06,520
and I won't let you
take the gaokao exams?

476
00:28:12,303 --> 00:28:15,823
I just want you
to have a change of scenery.

477
00:28:16,464 --> 00:28:17,343
That way,

478
00:28:18,624 --> 00:28:20,224
maybe you'll come around.

479
00:28:32,424 --> 00:28:35,144
Bai Shu, in the time you were away,

480
00:28:37,023 --> 00:28:38,583
I thought a lot too.

481
00:28:41,023 --> 00:28:44,783
Don't worry, I will definitely let you
come back for the exams.

482
00:28:46,704 --> 00:28:49,184
I just want both of us
to have a change of environment.

483
00:28:50,543 --> 00:28:52,464
I'm also tired of being in this room

484
00:28:53,303 --> 00:28:54,944
and endlessly fighting with you.

485
00:29:03,343 --> 00:29:05,103
I'm not your enemy.

486
00:29:05,743 --> 00:29:06,783
Everything I've done

487
00:29:07,424 --> 00:29:11,583
is to ensure you
live this life safely and happily.

488
00:29:14,063 --> 00:29:15,263
Do you hear me?

489
00:29:20,743 --> 00:29:23,184
Be good. Go change.

490
00:29:23,664 --> 00:29:24,864
Dress up nice and pretty.

491
00:29:31,263 --> 00:29:32,944
Bring everything you can, okay?

492
00:29:51,063 --> 00:29:51,783
Bai Shu?

493
00:29:53,184 --> 00:29:53,823
Bai Shu?

494
00:30:16,184 --> 00:30:16,684
Sir.

495
00:30:18,343 --> 00:30:18,904
What's up?

496
00:30:19,464 --> 00:30:20,792
Why are you driving Ms. Ge's car?

497
00:30:21,023 --> 00:30:23,664
I'm Ms. Ge's driver.
I just drove them to the airport.

498
00:30:23,904 --> 00:30:24,783
Where's Bai Shu?

499
00:30:24,823 --> 00:30:25,904
She went with her mom.

500
00:30:26,743 --> 00:30:27,768
They went to the airport?

501
00:30:27,864 --> 00:30:28,364
Yes.

502
00:30:30,424 --> 00:30:31,263
Where are they going?

503
00:30:31,864 --> 00:30:33,743
Leave. I can't tell you
where they're going.

504
00:30:33,752 --> 00:30:34,648
I'm closing the gate.

505
00:30:55,864 --> 00:30:57,944
- What are you doing?
- To get the magazine.

506
00:31:11,984 --> 00:31:12,783
Let's go.

507
00:31:14,624 --> 00:31:15,184
Coming.

508
00:31:29,823 --> 00:31:31,063
The cipher codes.

509
00:31:37,743 --> 00:31:39,224
110823.

510
00:31:39,664 --> 00:31:41,063
101921.

511
00:31:41,664 --> 00:31:43,904
870110.

512
00:31:45,458 --> 00:31:49,880
(Qingzhou, 2023)

513
00:32:08,583 --> 00:32:09,224
Add

514
00:32:14,023 --> 00:32:14,523
me

515
00:32:16,464 --> 00:32:17,023
now.

516
00:32:17,503 --> 00:32:19,263
I surrender myself.

517
00:32:20,783 --> 00:32:23,424
The unidentified deceased

518
00:32:24,464 --> 00:32:26,624
knew the truth.

519
00:32:35,506 --> 00:32:42,680
(Ren Xiaoming)

520
00:32:46,450 --> 00:32:49,368
(Ren Xiaoming. Send a message)

521
00:33:04,743 --> 00:33:05,783
(Finally made contact.)

522
00:33:06,624 --> 00:33:07,624
(No need to reply.)

523
00:33:08,263 --> 00:33:09,343
(Your seeing it is enough.)

524
00:33:23,944 --> 00:33:26,904
(Communication hours
are from 1 AM to 3 AM.)

525
00:33:27,103 --> 00:33:28,343
(Don't disturb at other times.)

526
00:33:34,962 --> 00:33:39,480
(Delete the chat with Ren Xiaoming)

527
00:33:59,144 --> 00:34:00,023
What's on your mind?

528
00:34:01,464 --> 00:34:02,704
The divorce agreement is ready.

529
00:34:02,783 --> 00:34:04,063
(Property Division Agreement)
Anything else to add?

530
00:34:05,904 --> 00:34:07,184
Let me give you a heads-up.

531
00:34:07,424 --> 00:34:10,143
The court is very unlikely
to grant the divorce.

532
00:34:10,464 --> 00:34:13,424
No affair, no domestic violence,
no external debt, no separation.

533
00:34:14,344 --> 00:34:15,784
And he doesn't want to divorce.

534
00:34:15,784 --> 00:34:17,344
The court likely won't grant it.

535
00:34:18,183 --> 00:34:19,063
I know.

536
00:34:19,663 --> 00:34:21,623
Then why aren't you focusing
on the key points?

537
00:34:21,744 --> 00:34:23,103
Key point one: divorce.

538
00:34:23,424 --> 00:34:24,744
Key point two: separation.

539
00:34:25,424 --> 00:34:25,924
No.

540
00:34:25,984 --> 00:34:27,444
Key point two: sue him.

541
00:34:30,183 --> 00:34:33,424
Ren Xiaoming,
divorce is a very long process.

542
00:34:33,784 --> 00:34:36,904
You know Liu Xiaoran has been building
this "good husband" image.

543
00:34:37,103 --> 00:34:38,543
If you divorce him so publicly,

544
00:34:38,663 --> 00:34:41,304
it'll only make you
the "poisonous woman' against 'good".

545
00:34:42,023 --> 00:34:44,264
Stir up a hornet's nest
and you'll get stung all over.

546
00:34:44,824 --> 00:34:47,023
Sometimes, bee venom
can be used medicinally.

547
00:34:48,023 --> 00:34:50,344
Sometimes only poison
is the cure to survive.

548
00:34:52,023 --> 00:34:55,183
My goodness,
what nonsense are you spouting?

549
00:34:55,183 --> 00:34:56,304
I really want to hit you.

550
00:34:57,784 --> 00:35:00,784
Only I'm willing to take on
these two losing lawsuits for you.

551
00:35:01,344 --> 00:35:05,023
Do you know how serious
a loss is for a lawyer?

552
00:35:05,424 --> 00:35:06,543
And it's consecutive losses.

553
00:35:06,944 --> 00:35:09,063
I, The Invincible One,
ended up becoming

554
00:35:09,304 --> 00:35:11,304
the Defeatable One just for you.

555
00:35:11,824 --> 00:35:13,344
Being defeatable isn't scary.

556
00:35:14,183 --> 00:35:15,264
Being lonely is.

557
00:35:15,944 --> 00:35:17,744
Alright, you have a point.

558
00:35:20,023 --> 00:35:20,583
Go for it.

559
00:35:22,183 --> 00:35:22,904
Love you.

560
00:35:28,503 --> 00:35:29,304
Pretty trendy.

561
00:35:29,304 --> 00:35:29,904
(Qidaohezi, 2007)
Looks great.

562
00:35:30,143 --> 00:35:30,744
Quite pretty.

563
00:35:31,784 --> 00:35:32,408
Do you want it?

564
00:35:32,824 --> 00:35:33,464
No.

565
00:35:33,656 --> 00:35:34,464
I can do a discount.

566
00:35:34,464 --> 00:35:35,160
I can...

567
00:35:35,264 --> 00:35:35,824
He Yuqiong.

568
00:35:36,304 --> 00:35:38,063
Only 25 yuan for each piece.

569
00:35:38,304 --> 00:35:39,864
Our store has various leather bags.

570
00:35:39,904 --> 00:35:40,824
Are you that busy?

571
00:35:41,464 --> 00:35:42,503
Too busy to say hello?

572
00:35:47,543 --> 00:35:49,424
Don't miss out if you're passing by.

573
00:35:49,623 --> 00:35:50,904
Eighteen yuan. Ten yuan.

574
00:35:51,103 --> 00:35:52,023
Well, sir.

575
00:35:52,023 --> 00:35:52,663
Which pair?

576
00:35:53,023 --> 00:35:53,583
How much?

577
00:35:54,023 --> 00:35:54,864
This pair? Eighteen.

578
00:35:55,223 --> 00:35:55,984
Eighteen is fine.

579
00:35:55,984 --> 00:35:56,484
Okay.

580
00:35:56,944 --> 00:35:57,444
Grab a bag.

581
00:36:04,183 --> 00:36:04,683
Sir,

582
00:36:05,663 --> 00:36:06,424
how much is this?

583
00:36:06,663 --> 00:36:07,503
It won't fit you.

584
00:36:10,824 --> 00:36:12,384
Take a look, have a look!

585
00:36:12,543 --> 00:36:13,063
The sweater?

586
00:36:13,583 --> 00:36:14,424
How much is it?

587
00:36:14,864 --> 00:36:15,824
This one? Fifty.

588
00:36:16,424 --> 00:36:17,424
Fifty? Make it cheaper.

589
00:36:17,864 --> 00:36:18,623
Sorry, I can't.

590
00:36:18,623 --> 00:36:19,784
Look, it's pure wool.

591
00:36:19,784 --> 00:36:20,344
Thirty.

592
00:36:20,663 --> 00:36:21,663
- Thirty?
- I'll take it.

593
00:36:21,663 --> 00:36:22,163
Deal.

594
00:36:22,744 --> 00:36:23,424
Great, thanks.

595
00:36:23,703 --> 00:36:24,744
Come back next time.

596
00:36:24,864 --> 00:36:25,864
What are you doing?

597
00:36:29,223 --> 00:36:30,344
What are you doing?

598
00:36:31,183 --> 00:36:32,103
Why ignore me?

599
00:36:33,063 --> 00:36:34,784
I'm busy making money. No time for you.

600
00:36:36,623 --> 00:36:37,143
What?

601
00:36:38,063 --> 00:36:40,344
I really need money right now.
No time for idle talk.

602
00:36:46,583 --> 00:36:49,543
I'm a customer.
Don't you have time for a customer?

603
00:36:49,944 --> 00:36:50,864
How much are the shoes?

604
00:36:51,143 --> 00:36:52,543
Nothing here fits you. Just go.

605
00:36:59,223 --> 00:37:00,264
(Big Sale During the Temple Fair)
Are you crazy?

606
00:37:02,264 --> 00:37:04,464
Would Bai Shu get beaten
after she went back?

607
00:37:06,904 --> 00:37:08,824
Did she go back because of our family?

608
00:37:10,944 --> 00:37:12,464
She had made up her mind long ago

609
00:37:13,623 --> 00:37:15,304
and even spent the New Year with us.

610
00:37:16,984 --> 00:37:17,904
Bai Shu

611
00:37:18,744 --> 00:37:19,543
always thinks of us.

612
00:37:19,543 --> 00:37:20,824
Can you please leave me alone?

613
00:37:21,143 --> 00:37:22,944
Are you done? You just keep nagging.

614
00:37:27,183 --> 00:37:29,103
Go back to your room. Don't stay here.

615
00:37:42,944 --> 00:37:43,583
Who is it?

616
00:37:51,183 --> 00:37:53,744
Ma'am, what brings you here?

617
00:37:54,143 --> 00:37:56,103
Tiantian told me your family lives here.

618
00:37:56,464 --> 00:37:57,424
It was easy to find.

619
00:37:58,944 --> 00:37:59,744
Is your mom home?

620
00:38:00,944 --> 00:38:01,744
She's out.

621
00:38:02,503 --> 00:38:03,424
Please come in.

622
00:38:07,503 --> 00:38:08,103
Have a seat.

623
00:38:13,543 --> 00:38:15,583
Xiaoming, you don't need to fuss.

624
00:38:15,744 --> 00:38:17,023
I need to hurry back.

625
00:38:19,543 --> 00:38:20,663
I came to return the money.

626
00:38:20,864 --> 00:38:23,543
When your mom gets back,
just give this money back to her for me.

627
00:38:24,223 --> 00:38:26,623
What money?

628
00:38:27,583 --> 00:38:30,344
The money spent on Tiantian
at the hospital last time.

629
00:38:30,663 --> 00:38:32,464
My mom asked you for money?

630
00:38:33,623 --> 00:38:36,424
The money should be repaid.
You can't blame your mom.

631
00:38:36,623 --> 00:38:37,784
Alright, I'm heading off now.

632
00:38:38,304 --> 00:38:38,984
Wait a minute.

633
00:38:40,784 --> 00:38:43,424
Is He Yuqiong mad at me because of this?

634
00:38:43,784 --> 00:38:45,424
How could he be mad at you?

635
00:38:46,103 --> 00:38:49,183
He's probably just afraid
of causing you trouble.

636
00:38:49,344 --> 00:38:51,864
His studies aren't great,

637
00:38:52,063 --> 00:38:54,703
and our family burden is quite heavy.

638
00:38:54,864 --> 00:38:56,623
Did Ren Meiyan tell you that?

639
00:38:56,864 --> 00:38:58,304
Did she try to sow discord?

640
00:38:58,663 --> 00:39:01,063
Xiaoming, your mom didn't say anything.

641
00:39:01,063 --> 00:39:02,464
I'm the one who said all this.

642
00:39:03,023 --> 00:39:04,103
She has it tough.

643
00:39:04,264 --> 00:39:04,944
We're both moms.

644
00:39:04,944 --> 00:39:07,663
I understand her well.
Especially since you're a girl.

645
00:39:08,464 --> 00:39:10,984
Isn't it normal
that she worries about you?

646
00:39:11,464 --> 00:39:12,824
You can't blame her, understand?

647
00:39:14,103 --> 00:39:16,264
Alright, I need to hurry back
to the stall.

648
00:39:47,264 --> 00:39:48,503
Xiaofei, dinner's ready.

649
00:39:50,984 --> 00:39:52,103
Alright, stop thinking.

650
00:39:52,344 --> 00:39:54,183
Bai Shu's return
must be part of her plan.

651
00:39:54,424 --> 00:39:57,264
Besides, there's still plenty of time.
We'll think of something.

652
00:40:03,344 --> 00:40:05,023
Xiaofei, I fried some bun slices.

653
00:40:09,944 --> 00:40:12,543
Don't look so miserable on New Year.
It's bad luck.

654
00:40:15,543 --> 00:40:16,663
I pan-fried some dumplings.

655
00:40:16,784 --> 00:40:17,904
Xiaofei, come eat. Xiaofei.

656
00:40:26,543 --> 00:40:27,744
Where'd you get all the money?

657
00:40:28,744 --> 00:40:30,424
Why did you
ask He Yuqiong's mom for money?

658
00:40:33,143 --> 00:40:33,824
It's my money.

659
00:40:33,824 --> 00:40:34,744
Why not ask for it?

660
00:40:35,543 --> 00:40:36,623
Why are you criticizing me?

661
00:40:36,864 --> 00:40:38,503
I'm your mother, and he's not my son.

662
00:40:39,023 --> 00:40:40,623
Why should I pay for his hospital stay?

663
00:40:40,623 --> 00:40:43,304
Money, money, money.
Is that all you think about all day?

664
00:40:44,663 --> 00:40:45,944
You can't talk to Mom like that.

665
00:40:47,264 --> 00:40:48,223
You pushed me!

666
00:40:48,223 --> 00:40:48,744
Stop it.

667
00:40:48,744 --> 00:40:49,503
What's it to you?

668
00:40:49,503 --> 00:40:50,392
What's wrong with you?

669
00:40:50,392 --> 00:40:50,784
Mom.

670
00:40:50,784 --> 00:40:51,663
What are you doing?

671
00:40:53,583 --> 00:40:54,703
This home is beyond saving.

672
00:40:55,623 --> 00:40:56,904
I'm leaving. I'm leaving.

673
00:40:57,183 --> 00:40:58,244
Xiaoming. Xiaoming.

674
00:40:58,904 --> 00:40:59,703
I'm leaving.

675
00:41:01,464 --> 00:41:02,023
Stop fighting.

676
00:41:02,143 --> 00:41:02,744
I'm leaving.

677
00:41:03,223 --> 00:41:03,784
Xiaoming.

678
00:41:04,464 --> 00:41:05,103
Stop fighting.

679
00:41:05,344 --> 00:41:07,344
Get away! Get away!

680
00:41:07,543 --> 00:41:08,384
Go away!

681
00:41:16,023 --> 00:41:17,824
It exploded. What was that sound?

682
00:41:19,183 --> 00:41:19,703
What's wrong?

683
00:41:22,784 --> 00:41:24,543
There's a fire downstairs!

684
00:41:25,023 --> 00:41:26,824
There was an explosion. What happened?

685
00:41:26,964 --> 00:41:27,464
What?

686
00:41:27,464 --> 00:41:29,264
The video store is on fire!

687
00:41:29,503 --> 00:41:30,583
The video store is on fire!

688
00:41:30,744 --> 00:41:32,023
Xiaoming! Xiaoming! Xiaoming!

689
00:41:32,023 --> 00:41:32,663
Come out quick!

690
00:41:32,663 --> 00:41:33,163
Mom!

691
00:41:33,223 --> 00:41:34,503
Mom, you can't go! Mom!

692
00:41:41,663 --> 00:41:42,304
Where is it?

693
00:41:42,904 --> 00:41:44,304
The video store is on fire?

694
00:41:46,223 --> 00:41:47,223
The fire engine is here.

695
00:41:49,143 --> 00:41:50,264
It's Zhang Fang's place.

696
00:41:50,264 --> 00:41:51,264
Is Zhang Fang's mom okay?

697
00:41:52,984 --> 00:41:54,264
I wonder how Zhang Fang is.

698
00:41:54,424 --> 00:41:55,143
Xiaoming!

699
00:42:04,304 --> 00:42:05,063
The ambulance.

700
00:42:05,424 --> 00:42:06,264
Don't go over there!

701
00:42:06,703 --> 00:42:07,703
Make way! Make way!

702
00:42:07,703 --> 00:42:08,583
Everyone, move back!

703
00:42:10,223 --> 00:42:11,464
Don't go over. It's dangerous.

704
00:42:12,183 --> 00:42:15,223
(Zhang Fang's family used too much water
when braising pork hocks.)

705
00:42:16,304 --> 00:42:18,872
(Water overflowed the pot
and extinguished the stove.)

706
00:42:20,760 --> 00:42:24,183
(People were playing cards
and forgot the pork hocks on the stove.)

707
00:42:25,424 --> 00:42:27,824
(The pork hocks' aroma
and the firecrackers' sulfur smell)

708
00:42:28,424 --> 00:42:29,583
(masked the smell of gas.)

709
00:42:32,304 --> 00:42:35,183
(That night, Zhang Fang was playing
at a classmate's place)

710
00:42:35,984 --> 00:42:36,984
(and dodged it.)

711
00:42:38,304 --> 00:42:39,904
(But he lost all his family)

712
00:42:41,183 --> 00:42:42,223
(and his home.)

713
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,808
=Vanished Name=
